<emphasis id="D3D117D6A1153AECAA448FA5C9707081" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hypocrella bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(K(M)52469, isotype, images are accredited to the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew) 
<emphasis id="554C7751FD812BB6C2F6BF53C427000E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A, C</emphasis>
fruiting bodies on inflorescence of bamboo 
<emphasis id="8A36FBFE5ED0B3193258BB03C4774855" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
vertical section of stromata showing the perithecia locating 
<emphasis id="CBDA510D637F5358A661A7DC1E9622F3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
herbarium envelope 
<emphasis id="2FD6D7A91F67CCB14B712BC1827BE41F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E</emphasis>
filiform ascospores 
<emphasis id="ED6F5F75A9522FD844F39CE4AF0BEC5F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F</emphasis>
asci with caps (Staining by cotton blue). Scale bars: 5 mm (
<emphasis id="2BA12553560D1F86D9E180DA232EA60C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
), 200 
<normalizedToken id="90BC290ADFD18CB7A974610F12BDC3DD" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="1A08BB30EA774518F3970C23139F69ED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
), 2 mm (
<emphasis id="4D4875486643F05E882A62B068CF5436" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
), 20 
<normalizedToken id="99F42652E65E94BF12163444BE30ED40" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="02D56383C67AEF09A8D22826D9672B79" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E, F</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
