<subSubSection id="18508C01A6DA5279816DE1BB37FA2A59" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B3DA8FB5D95294D7315F89D78F6B8E14" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14B88CF52D67142A26CC80FE57D230FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This taxon has typical morphology of the 
<taxonomicName id="BA0CA8A83E3E875D79B196BE3A61D504" genus="Clavicipitaceae" lsidName="Clavicipitaceae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FA1A0D110CFD4046ED06CE0AF0B5FF30" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Clavicipitaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is pyriform perithecia with a gradually tapering upper part and cylindrical asci with a glassy refractive cap. New collections are required and need to be sequenced to clarify its placement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
